    //- Course Overview
    .row.mb-4
      .col-lg-8
        h3 Course Overview
        p This course trains master's level computer science students to become Silicon Valley-ready software engineers in the age of AI. Students will master AI-assisted development tools while maintaining professional engineering standards, learning to build high-quality, production-ready full-stack applications.
        p Building successful software with AI requires more than good prompting—it demands understanding how Large Language Models work, when to use which tools, how to evaluate AI-generated code systematically, and how to integrate AI into professional development workflows.

        .alert.alert-info.mt-3
          strong Hybrid Format:
          |  This course is offered in-person at Oakland Campus and via Zoom for remote students. The instructor has extensive experience teaching remotely, ensuring a great experience for all students regardless of location.

        h4.mt-4 Why This Course?
        .row
          .col-md-6
            ul
              li #[strong Industry-Relevant]: Tools and practices used in top tech companies
              li #[strong Portfolio-Focused]: Build 3 prototype applications for your portfolio
              li #[strong Comprehensive]: LLM fundamentals, prompt engineering, evals, TDD, CI/CD
          .col-md-6
            ul
              li #[strong Balanced]: Learn AI-assisted coding AND prove you can code without AI
              li #[strong Future-Proof]: Master the workflow, not just current tools

      .col-lg-4
        .card
          .card-body
            h5.card-title Instructor
            p.mb-1 #[a(href="https://johnguerra.co") John Alexis Guerra Gómez]
            p.mb-1
              small
                a#email-link(href="#") [Enable JavaScript to see email]
            hr
            p.mb-1 #[strong Office Hours]
            p.mb-0 By appointment via Slack

    //- The Three AI Modalities
    .row.mb-4
      .col-12
        h3 The Three AI Modalities
        p Students will master three distinct AI coding paradigms:
      .col-md-4
        .modality-card.modality-claude-web
          h5 Modality 1: Claude Web
          p.small.mb-1 #[strong Best for:] Architecture planning, learning, complex problem-solving
          p.small.mb-0 #[strong Skills:] Claude Projects, artifacts, conversational iteration
      .col-md-4
        .modality-card.modality-antigravity
          h5 Modality 2: Antigravity
          p.small.mb-1 #[strong Best for:] Professional development, production code, daily workflow
          p.small.mb-0 #[strong Skills:] Tab autocomplete, Composer, .antigravityrules, YOLO mode
      .col-md-4
        .modality-card.modality-claude-code
          h5 Modality 3: Claude Code
          p.small.mb-1 #[strong Best for:] Automation, multi-file refactoring, DevOps
          p.small.mb-0 #[strong Skills:] Terminal workflows, autonomous agents, script automation

    //- Projects
    .row.mb-4#projects
      .col-12
        h3 Portfolio Projects
        p.text-muted All projects are open topic—you choose what to build after getting instructor approval.
      .col-md-4
        .project-card.project-p1
          h5 Project 1: Personal Utility App
          p.small Build a personal utility application that solves a real problem validated through Mom Test interviews.
          ul.small
            li 5+ user stories with CRUD operations
            li Basic test suite (50%+ coverage)
            li GitHub Actions CI pipeline
            li Deployed and publicly accessible
          span.badge(style="background-color: var(--color-green)") 13% of grade
          span.badge.ms-1(style="background-color: var(--color-green-light); color: #333") Due Week 6
      .col-md-4
        .project-card.project-p2
          h5 Project 2: Full-Stack Application
          p.small Complete full-stack application using multiple AI modalities, Agile practices, TDD, and production-grade CI/CD.
          ul.small
            li User authentication (JWT/OAuth)
            li Test-Driven Development (80%+ coverage)
            li Comprehensive evaluation suite
            li 2 documented Agile sprints
          span.badge(style="background-color: var(--color-purple)") 18% of grade
          span.badge.ms-1(style="background-color: var(--color-purple-light); color: #333") Due Week 10
      .col-md-4
        .project-card.project-p3
          h5 Project 3: Production App with Claude Code Mastery
          p.small Pair project: deploy a production-grade app demonstrating mastery of Claude Code extensibility (W10-W14).
          ul.small
            li CLAUDE.md, skills, hooks, MCP, agents
            li TDD + CI/CD with AI PR review
            li Vercel deployment + Sentry monitoring
            li Blog post + screencast + live demo
          span.badge(style="background-color: var(--color-orange)") 19% of grade
          span.badge.ms-1(style="background-color: var(--color-orange-light); color: #333") Due Week 15

